article.description: Chris Clemons scored 30 points on 10-of-11 shooting and Campbell set a school home-court record for most points scored in a 110-66 rout of NAIA member Allen University in a non-conference matchup
article.headline: Campbell takes down NAIA-member Allen (S.C.) 110-66
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Chris Clemons scored 30 points on 10-of-11 shooting and Campbell set a school home-court record for most points scored in a 110-66 rout of NAIA member Allen University in a non-conference matchup Tuesday night. The tally beats the 101 points the Camels scored against Methodist on Dec. 10, 2011 in the Gilbert Craig Gore Arena. Clemons became the first Campbell freshman to score more than 30-plus points three times in a season. The Camels shot 74.5 percent (38 of 51) from the field, a school record in the Division I era. Rod Days and Casey Perrin scored 14 points apiece, a career high for Perrin, and Khadre Lane and Kyre' Hamer added 11 each for the Camels (11-15). Campbell trailed briefly but led 55-37 at halftime behind Clemons' 24 points on 75 percent shooting from the field. Ivory Drummond led the Yellow Jackets with 17 points.
